{
  "texts": [
    "In a recent advancement, a conditional generative pretrained transformer model, cMolGPT, was designed for the autoregressive generation of target-specific de novo molecules using natural language processing (NLP) techniques (Wang et al., 2023b).",
    "This model was initially pretrained on an extensive SMILES dataset, enabling it to learn the parametric probabilistic distribution of druglike properties (e.g., LogP and molecular weight), across the SMILES vocabulary space in an unsupervised manner.",
    "The cMolGPT model incorporates a of key-value pairs within the transformer architecture, which is further enforced by target-specific embeddings to facilitate the conditional generation of multihead attention for drug-like compounds.",
    "The findings revealed that cMolGPT is adept at generating SMILES strings that represent both drug-like and active compounds.",
    "In addition, the generated The workflow of Chemformer."
  ]
}